  "text": "Following other real-time semantic segmentation methods [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , we adopt the mean Intersection over Union (mIoU) and frames per second (fps) for single forward propagation as our evaluation metrics, which are used to evaluate the accuracy and speed of all the competing methods. Moreover, the number of parameters (Params) and float-point operations (FLOPs) are also used to evaluate the memory consumption and computational complexity, respectively.",
